snippet.textDisplay: Thank you for mentioning Putnam County and showing photos. I live in Cookeville, TN and it's horrible. Out of the 25 deaths, 18 were here and 5 were children under the age of 13 along with 13 adults, a lot the parents...entire families. But this morning over 2,000 people showed up at 8 a.m. to the designated site for volunteers and mobilized and went out into the community with chainsaws, trucks and supplies. Local restaurants are giving away meals. Shelters are set up everywhere. Car dealerships are loaning out trucks and Uhaul is donating trucks and trailers. It's one positive thing to see in all of this. Yesterday the lines were blocks long at blood donation centers. We still have 22 people missing that we are aware of and many are without power and water. We are the furthest town from Nashville that was impacted and I haven't seen much media attention for us in comparison with that covering Nashville and it's surrounding towns. So again, thank you.
